# Multi-server Redis Cluster configuration
#
# Format: server_ip  node_numbers (comma-separated)
#
# Place a master and a replica of a DIFFERENT master on each server
# so that losing one server doesn't lose both copies of any data.
#
# Example: 3 servers, 6 nodes (3 masters + 3 replicas)
# Redis assigns masters to the first 3 nodes, replicas to the last 3.
# Nodes 1,2,3 = masters; Nodes 4,5,6 = replicas.
# Node 4 replicates a different master than node 1, etc.

192.168.1.10  1,4
192.168.1.11  2,5
192.168.1.12  3,6
